Class BootstrapFeedbackPopover

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Iterable<org.apache.wicket.Component>, org.apache.wicket.event.IEventSink, org.apache.wicket.event.IEventSource, org.apache.wicket.feedback.IFeedback, org.apache.wicket.feedback.IFeedbackContributor, org.apache.wicket.IConverterLocator, org.apache.wicket.markup.html.IHeaderContributor, org.apache.wicket.request.component.IRequestableComponent, org.apache.wicket.util.IHierarchical<org.apache.wicket.Component>, org.apache.wicket.util.io.IClusterable

    public class BootstrapFeedbackPopover
extends org.apache.wicket.markup.html.WebMarkupContainer
implements org.apache.wicket.feedback.IFeedback
    Display feedback messages of a FormComponent with a Bootstrap Popover on the component.

     

     

    Example: 
            <div class="control-group" wicket:id="feedback">
          <input wicket:id="input" type="text" />
  </div>

     

    Java code: 
       add(new BootstrapFeedbackPopover("feedback").add(new TextField<String>("input")));

     

    NOTE: this popover has a special html class 'feedback-popover' to create custom css.

     

    Author:
    acamilo
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
